main event: A witness reported an unusual meteor sighting in Bellbrook, Ohio on August 5, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared yellow-green with a tail.,The meteor moved at high speed for an estimated 3 to 5 seconds.,Witness regarded the observation as unusual rather than a UFO.,The object moved in a straight line.,There were no physical evidence or photographs associated with the report.
witnesses: a 44-year-old male, identified as a Fight Dynamics Lab man and satellite observer
